 As rescue efforts continued throughout the Nepalese capital , more than 1,000 passengers joined a haphazard 1km-long queue outside the nearby airport in a desperate attempt to flee the stricken city .
Despite plummeting temperatures and rain , crowds had started to form outside Tribhuwan International Airport .
Many visitors had already booked return journeys but crowds had form outside the airport .
The airport is in waiting area to accommodate travellers .